{{italic title}}
The '''''Biographie nationale de Belgique''''' ([[French language|French]]; "National Biography of Belgium") is a [[biographical dictionary]] of [[Belgium]]. It was published by the [[Royal Academies for Science and the Arts of Belgium|Royal Academy of Belgium]] in 44 volumes between 1866 and 1986. A continuation series, entitled the '''''Nouvelle Biographie Nationale''''' ("New National Biography"), has been published by the [[Royal Academy of Science, Letters and Fine Arts of Belgium]] since 1988. Both the ''Biographie nationale'' and ''Nouvelle biographie nationale'' were digitised by the Fonds InBev-Baillet Latour and can be freely consulted at the Academy's website.

A parallel biographical dictionary has been produced in [[Dutch language|Dutch]] since 1964, entitled the ''Nationaal Biografisch Woordenboek'' ("National Biographical Dictionary"). It places more emphasis on figures important to the history and culture of [[Flanders]] and is published by the [[Royal Flemish Academy of Belgium for Science and the Arts]] (with the co-operation of the [[Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature]] and the [[Royal Academy of Medicine of Belgium]]). 

