The '''Democratic Renewal Party''' ({{Lang-pt|Partido da Renovação Democrática}}, PRD) was a centrist [[political party]] in [[Cape Verde]].

==History==
The PRD was established in 2000 by Jacinto Santos, a former member of the [[Movement for Democracy (Cape Verde)|Movement for Democracy]], who had served as mayor of [[Praia]].<ref name=HDCV>Richard A Lobban Jr & Paul Khalil Saucier (2007) ''Historical Dictionary of the Republic of Cape Verde'', Scarecrow Press, p181</ref> The party received 3.4% of the vote in the [[Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2001|2001 elections]], but failed to win a seat in the [[National Assembly (Cape Verde)|National Assembly]]. Its vote share subsequently fell to 0.7% in the [[Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2006|2006 parliamentary elections]].

