'''Radio 1''' is a public radio station in [[Accra]], the capital town of the [[Greater Accra Region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref name=Radio>{{cite web|title=Radio|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/communication/radio.php|publisher=www.ghanaweb.com|accessdate=10 March 2012}}</ref> The station is owned and run by the state broadcaster - the [[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]] (GBC).<ref name=GBC>{{cite web|title=Ghana Broadcasting Cooperation|url=http://www.gbcghana.com/|publisher=www.gbcghana.com|accessdate=10 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=RW>{{cite web|title=Radio Station World|url=http://radiostationworld.com/locations/ghana/Radio.asp|publisher=www.radiostationworld.com|accessdate=10 March 2012}}</ref> The station is one of two national stations run by GBC. The station broadcasts in English and other Ghanaian languages including Akan, Dagbani, Ewe, Ga, Hausa and Nzema.<ref name=Radio/>
